To run bootstrapping and Hearst patterns scripts use
the format explained in perldoc. To get more details, type

perldoc ./bootstrapping.pl
perldoc ./hearst_patterns_fiad.pl

or

./bootstrapping.pl -h
./hearst_patterns_fiad.pl -h

The scripts are modified in such a way that a data set in plain *txt is used as input (rather than the output from Indri/Lemur).

To run a toy example included here, type

./hearst_patterns_fiad.pl -t protein -p myhearst.txt -w stop_words.txt -d mycorpus -n 20 -o myseeds > myseeds.log
./bootstrapping_final.pl -m 3 -n myseeds -d mycorpus -k 5 -p mypatterns > mypatterns.log 

Tested under Perl v5.8.5 built for i686-linux